<div class="content-page">
  <div class="content-page__inner">
    <h1 class="content-page__title">Support</h1>
    <p class="content-page__intro">Need help with Math Direct? Here is how to get answers, report problems, and suggest improvements.</p>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-section__title">Check the Guide First</h2>
      <p>Most questions about how lessons work, error correction, and session tips are covered in the <a href="/guide/">Teacher &amp; Parent Guide</a>. If you are new to Math Direct, start there.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-section__title">Report a Bug</h2>
      <p>Found something broken? Open an issue on our <a href="https://github.com/jonajinga/math-direct/issues">GitHub Issues</a> page. Please include:</p>
      <ul class="guide-tips">
        <li>The lesson number (if applicable)</li>
        <li>What you expected to happen</li>
        <li>What actually happened</li>
        <li>Your browser and device (e.g., Chrome on iPad)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-section__title">Suggest an Improvement</h2>
      <p>Have an idea for a new feature or a better way to teach a concept? Open a <a href="https://github.com/jonajinga/math-direct/issues">GitHub issue</a> with the label "enhancement" or email us directly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-section__title">Email</h2>
      <p>For general questions or feedback, reach us at <a href="mailto:hello@mathdirect.com">hello@mathdirect.com</a>. We respond within two business days.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-section__title">Contributing</h2>
      <p>Math Direct is open source. If you want to contribute code, fix a typo, or improve a lesson, visit the <a href="https://github.com/jonajinga/math-direct">GitHub repository</a> and submit a pull request.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
